data.title: Visit Hodgenville, Kentucky – Abraham Lincoln…and a lot more!
data.text:
Experience the Best in Kentucky at Abraham Lincoln’s birthplace.

Lincoln Birthplace

See where the story began at Abraham Lincoln Birthplace National Historical Park.

The Lincoln Museum

Walk through Lincoln’s life at Kentucky’s Official Tribute to Abraham Lincoln, The Lincoln Museum.

Lincoln Boyhood Home

Enjoy the outdoor beauty of Knob Creek and special exhibits at Lincoln’s Boyhood Home.

Lincoln Days

Voted “Best Festival” by the readers of Kentucky Living. Join us October 5-6, 2024 for Lincoln Days.

Area Businesses

Learn more about the unique businesses that call LaRue County home at LaRue County Chamber of Commerce.

Places to Eat

You’ll never leave hungry on a visit to Hodgenville. View our online list of restaurants here or download a list of area restaurants.

Come enjoy Abraham Lincoln… and a lot more in Hodgenville.
